-- Santander Brasil CEO sees local loan market 'returning to normal'
-- By Aluísio Alves
-- Thu Jan 30, 2014 07:46AM EST
-- None



SAO PAULO, Jan 30 (Reuters) - Local credit markets in Brazil are "returning to normal", with margins recovering from a decline in recent years and loan defaults receding, Jesús Zabalza, chief executive officer of Banco Santander Brasil SA <SANB11.SA> said on Thursday.   (Reporting by Aluísio Alves; Writing by Guillermo Parra-Bernal; Editing by Sophie Hares)  ((guillermo.parra@thomsonreuters.com)(+55-11-5644-7714)(+55-119 -8346-7153)(Reuters Messaging: guillermo.parra.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: SANTANDER BRAZIL/CEO

